                        <td>
                        
                            <h1><strong>The IGC&#39;s 2023 call for proposals is now open!</strong></h1>
<br/>
The International Growth Centre (IGC) is pleased to announce a <a href="https://www.theigc.org/funding/call-for-proposals" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">new call for proposals</a>. Researchers are invited to submit proposals for research projects relevant to <strong>promoting sustainable growth in developing countries</strong>.<br/>
<br/>
We encourage any researcher to apply, but in particular PhD students, early career researchers, and researchers based in developing countries. The deadline for submissions is <strong>17:00 GMT on 14 November 2023</strong>.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody></table>
				
                
				
            </td>
        </tr>
    
</tbody></table><table>
    
	
        <tbody><tr>
            <td>
                
				
                <table>
                    <tbody><tr>
                        
                        <td>
                        
                            <table>
                                <tbody><tr>
                                    <td>
                                        <strong>At a glance</strong>

<ul>
	<li>The IGC is currently accepting proposals from from any researcher with projects focused on sustainable growth policies across our four themes:

	<ul>
		<li>Firms, trade, and productivity</li>
		<li>State effectiveness</li>
		<li>Cities</li>
		<li>Energy and environment </li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>We offer two types of awards: <strong>full research grants</strong> and <strong>small research grants</strong>.</li>
	<li>The deadline is <a href="https://www.theigc.org/funding/call-for-proposals/how-to-apply" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><strong>17:00 GMT on 14 November 2023</strong></a>.</li>
	<li>We strongly encourage research in <strong><a href="https://www.theigc.org/where-we-work" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">IGC resident countries</a>.</strong></li>
</ul>


                                    </td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody></table>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody></table>
				
                
				
            </td>
        </tr>
    
</tbody></table><table>
    
